I like the feel and performance of this brush. For the first week, I didn't try to use it, but rather just loaded the brush with soap, worked up a lather in my cupped palm, and then rinsed the brush well. This is based on my previous experience with boar brushes, which initially don't hold a lather. After a week, I started using it for real, and found that is performs well and feels good on my face. Thanks to the very nice handle, it also feels good in my hand.
Large Brush, very little backbone with very soft dense knot

I think it is a great quality brush. However, it is a large brush, has fine bristles, and once broken in, does not have a lot of backbone. I personally like Boars because of the backbone on the brush, so this brush doesn't work for me. If this is what you like, great. I added rubber O rings to shorten the loft considerably to give more backbone and reduce the splay to the brush, making it better for face lathering and my own personal preference. If you are looking for lots of backbone, this is not the brush for you. But this is a well made, fine product and those looking for soft bristles with a large knot and lots of easy splay should enjoy this brush.
